article.story: SEATTLE -- — John Christofilis scored 22 points as Seattle beat Portland State 91-74 on Wednesday. Christofilis shot 7 for 13 (4 for 6 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line for the Redhawks (3-5). Paris Dawson shot 6 for 7 (4 for 5 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line to add 19 points. Matthew-Alexander Moncrieffe added 15 points and 10 rebounds. Qiant Myers led the way for the Vikings (4-4) with 15 points and six assists. Isaiah Johnson added 13 points and six rebounds for Portland State. Shane Nowell also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
